    "verdict": "ok",
    "note": "Approved. 56 vocab + 68 grammar across three structures — possessive pronouns (24), possessive 's (23), Who/Whose questions (21). Grant: broke (SB who-question example; possessive pronouns mine/yours/his/hers/ours/theirs/whose are bank words). GRADER CONTRACT (Track B note for Koki): six possessive-'s / possessive-pronoun selection items distinguish options by apostrophe — these require an apostrophe-AWARE grader; per docs/handover/02 the documented canonicalization strips only trailing .!? and does NOT strip apostrophes, so they grade correctly (confirmed). Smoke-check fixed 5 possessive-pronoun definitions that circularly leaked the possessive adjective (his/her/our/their/your inflect to the pronoun), a formal \"Ihre\" → du-form, a duplicate-left matching item, and an apostrophe-malformed distractor. Verify round 1: replaced a true-synonym distractor (carry/transport), reworded tree-house off the name-masked \"oak\", and demoted plural/infinitive forms that broke their carriers; round 2 added strict to four Who/Whose & yours/ours gap-fills (the contrast word was within the Levenshtein budget). 22 glosses (home/material domain) + 62 translations adjudicated. NOTE: gloss-heavy (~22 tokens) — home/material vocab (made/water/animal/stripes) is untaught yet needed. rejectRate 0.0%."
